# PowerEdge R410 profile.
#
# Chassis notes:
# - 1U with 6× 40mm fans (FAN MOD 1A/B, 2A/B, 3A/B)
# - DANGER: BMC obeys low PWM literally — 5% = 0 RPM (fan stall, zero
#   airflow). No safety clamp like R730xd. MIN_FAN must stay >=15 to
#   avoid stalling. Probed values: 10%=840 RPM (suspicious), 15%=2520
#   RPM (safe minimum), 20%=3600 RPM (current default).
# - No GPU
# - CPUs are Xeon 5500/5600 series, TJunction ~95-100°C
# - IMPORTANT: BMC reports IPMI entity 3.x as "Disabled" — relies on
#   coretemp source via /sys/class/hwmon (controller handles fallback)

: "${MIN_FAN:=20}"             # 20% = 3600 RPM. Probed lower (15% = 2520
                               # RPM) but BMC flagged "lcr" (lower-critical
                               # threshold breach) and IPMI started returning
                               # comms errors. 20% is the operational floor
                               # on R410 — BMC is OK with it.
